address: Xã Cam Tân, Huyện Cam Lâm, Tỉnh Khánh Hòa
thought:
**Analysis of "Xã Cam Tân" Mapping in Khánh Hòa Province**

Okay, so I'm tackling this address, "Xã Cam Tân, Huyện Cam Lâm, Tỉnh Khánh Hòa," and need to map it to the new administrative structure. First, the province is straightforward, "Tỉnh Khánh Hòa," and resolution 60-NQ/TW confirms that name.

The tricky part is "Xã Cam Tân." I'm looking through relevant resolutions. Resolution 1667/NQ-UBTVQH15 (Khánh Hòa) is where the key lies. I see "Xã Cam Tân" appearing multiple times as part of the composition of *other* new wards:

*   Line 18 mentions "Xã Cam Tân" being incorporated into the new "Xã Cam Lâm."
*   Line 19 shows "Xã Cam Tân" is used to form the new "Xã Suối Dầu."
*   Line 20 indicates "Xã Cam Tân" (or rather, the remaining part of it) being a component of the new "Xã Cam Hiệp."

However, only "Xã Cam Lâm" is found in the "New Wards" list with the associated ward code of "22453". Resolution 1678/NQ-UBTVQH15 (Nghệ An) and 1686/NQ-UBTVQH15 (Thanh Hóa) are irrelevant since they deal with different places.

Therefore, "Xã Cam Tân" is part of the new "Xã Cam Lâm," with the provided ward code "22453." The analysis indicates that there will need further research in order to understand how much of the old area makes up the new "Xã Cam Lâm".
